OL,3,CFamily say surgery for 'locked jaw'
OL,4,Cwould transform daughter's life
OL,6,FShe has spent 15 years trying to get a
OL,7,Fdiagnosis and treatment plan for the
OL,8,Fdebilitating jaw condition.
OL,10,FHer family say she was told her pain
OL,11,Fwas likely muscular, caused by her
OL,12,Fclenching or grinding her teeth.
OL,14,FBut she was misdiagnosed and has now
OL,15,Fbeen diagnosed with late stage (TMD).
OL,17,FThis means her jaw joint is
OL,18,Fcatastrophically damaged, and her only
OL,19,Foption is a full replacement.
